Makes 1 large 12-14 inch pan

Ingredents
  1 lb Hamburger (or spicy sausage to taste)
  2 cans tomato sauce
  2 cans diced tomatoes – (blended to desired consistency)
  1 clove garlic
  2 T dried Parsley flakes
  1 tsp sugar
  1 tsp dried basil leaves
  1/2 tsp salt
  lasagna noodles (uncooked)
  1 - 16 oz carton ricotta or cottage cheese
  1/4 cup parmesan cheese
  1 1/2 tsp dried oregano leaves
  2 T dried parsley flakes
  Mozzarella cheese
  1/4 cup grated parmesan cheese


Brown hamburger, drain, add sauce and tomatoes and first batch of seasonings.   
Heat to boiling, let simmer stirring occasionally. 

Put ricotta or cottage cheese in bowl and add seasonings.  Stir well.

In large baking dish spread thin layer of sauce.  Reserveing for the last step 1 Cup sauce and 1 Cup Mozzarella.  
Place 1 layer of Lasagna noodles on bottom of dish.  
Layer 1/3 each remaining Sauce mixture, mozzarella cheese and ricotta cheese.  
Repeat 2 times.  Place a last layer of noodles.  
Spoon remaining sauce and mozzarella over the top.  
Sprinkle with ¼ cup parmesan cheese.   
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until fork tender.   
Let set for 10 minutes before serving.
Enjoy!
